rComments: Dr. Arbour likes VERY detailed answers and expects students to memorize all the details, except that she doesn't tell you at first. What she mentions in lectures and on the marking rubrics does NOT match her expectations. Always go for an extra mile and try to read her mind for a good grade, also don't expect a remark on the tests.

Can't control her class. The course curriculum needs work. UofT says they don't bell-curve but they definitely do. She clearly loves her research. That being said, she is a researcher and not a teacher.
